---
description: Enforces use of matchQueryStatus utility for handling TanStack Query states in React client components to replace imperative loading/error/empty/success logic with declarative pattern for improved readability and maintainability
globs: **/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---

Query Status Handling:
- Use `matchQueryStatus` utility for query states
- Replace imperative if/else status logic
- Handle Loading, Errored, Empty, Success states
- Keep components declarative and clean
- Maintain consistent query handling patterns

Anti-patterns:
- Avoid multiple return statements for status
- Avoid imperative `isLoading`/`isError` checks
- Don't repeat layout wrapper components
- Never use cluttered conditional rendering

Example:
```tsx
export function PostsList() {
  const postsQuery = usePostsListQuery();

  return (
    <PostsListLayout>
      {matchQueryStatus(postsQuery, {
        Loading: <LoadingSpinner />,
        Errored: (error) => <ErrorMessage error={error.message} />,
        Empty: <EmptyMessage message="No posts found." />,
        Success: ({ data }) => (
          <ul>
            {data.map((post) => (
              <li key={post.id}>{post.title}</li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        ),
      })}
    </PostsListLayout>
  );
}
```